Please ignore my previous comment. The answer should be "No" after I reviewed the Azure Policy "Allowed locations for resource group":
 "policyRule": {
 "if": {
 "allOf": [
 {
 "field": "type",
 "equals": "Microsoft.Resources/subscriptions/resourceGroups"
 },
 {
 "field": "location",
 "notIn": "[parameters('listOfAllowedLocations')]"
 }
 ]
 },

This policy only applies to RG in policy definition. Even though it can be inherited/cascaded, it won't limit other resources inside the RG because it specifies "RG" only.
